body:
## Problem statement

This all started with this error: 400 Bad Request: "{\"code\":400,\"message\":\"parsing body body from \\"\\" failed, because siteType in body is required\"}"

I confirmed that my JSON input had the siteType field present, then traced the generated code and found this:

```
func (m *SRN) UnmarshalJSON(raw []byte) error {
    var data struct { ... }
    if err := json.Unmarshal(raw, &data); err != nil {
        return err
    }
    site, err := UnmarshalSite(bytes.NewBuffer(raw), httpkit.JSONConsumer())
    if err != nil {
        return err
    }
```

Essentially, the raw "SRN" byteslice is being passed to be unmarshalled as Site, which will obviously fail, since SRN has no property called "siteType".

If I modify the generated "Site" code, as follows, it works

before 

```
func unmarshalSite(data []byte, consumer httpkit.Consumer) (Site, error) {
    buf := bytes.NewBuffer(data)
    buf2 := bytes.NewBuffer(data)
    // the first time this is read is to fetch the value of the siteType property.
    var getType struct {
        SiteType string json:"siteType"
    }
    if err := consumer.Consume(buf, &getType); err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }    if err := validate.RequiredString("siteType", "body", getType.SiteType); err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }
```

after

```
var getType struct {
        Site struct {
            SiteType string `json:"siteType"`
        } `json:"site"`
    }
    if err := consumer.Consume(buf, &getType); err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }
    if err := validate.RequiredString("siteType", "body", getType.Site.SiteType); err != nil {
        return nil, err
    }
```
